-- U.K. Water Company Pennon’s Waste Unit Acquires Pulp Friction
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-10-09T08:57:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-09/u-k-water-company-pennon-s-waste-unit-acquires-pulp-friction.html
Pennon Group Plc (PNN) , the U.K.’s third-
biggest publicly trading water company, said today that its
Viridor unit acquired Pulp Friction Ltd. to expand further in
waste management and recycling.  Pennon, which also owns South West Water Ltd., the water
and sewer services provider for Devon, Cornwall and parts of
Dorset, said Viridor purchased the Kent paper collection and
processing business for 9 million pounds ($14.4 million).  United Utilities Group Plc (UU/)  is the largest publicly traded
water company in Britain, followed by Severn Trent Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
